=========================
Program stucture
=========================

ROOT/stringClient.cc
ROOT/stringServer.cc

ROOT/src/tcpstream.cc
ROOT/src/tcpconnector.cc
ROOT/src/tcpacceptor.cc

ROOT/include/HEADER_FILES
ROOT/Makefile
ROOT/src/Makefile

=========================
Compiling
=========================

> cd ROOT_DIR
> make

This will generate `./stringServer` and `./stringClient`

=========================
Cleaning
=========================

> cd ROOT_DIR
> make clean

=========================
Running
=========================

> ./stringServer

This will start a tcp server on a random port and will display the servers hostname and port number.

> ./stringClient

This will read the `SERVER_ADDRESS` and `SERVER_PORT` environment variables and attempt to connect to the server
